Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.33,0:00:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll get back to these questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.84,0:00:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see, spiritual truth doesn't come out of historical cause and effectness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.85,0:00:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the downside of religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.74,0:00:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's back there, and it's there.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.07,0:00:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The upside of religion is that it embodies
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.82,0:00:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the acknowledgement of holiness and sacredness,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.94,0:00:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the respect for that which is sacred.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.70,0:00:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The one thing religion does get is the divinity of God
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.25,0:00:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and the sacredness of that divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.60,0:00:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The great cathedrals of the world, which, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.14,0:00:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,right now we're calibrating a thousand things.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.79,0:00:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,She's calibrating a thousand things.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.15,0:00:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm asking a thousand questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.21,0:00:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, when you calibrate the great cathedrals of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.43,0:00:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,they're high, 700s.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.14,0:01:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,700 is very, very unlikely as an occurrence in this planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.51,0:01:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Few are the beings who ever even reach 700.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.06,0:01:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But the great cathedrals, Chartres,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.12,0:01:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the great cathedrals are stunning.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.70,0:01:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When you walk into them, you're enveloped in this aura of sacredness,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.26,0:01:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,worship, devotion, and the energy of that prevails.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.85,0:01:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hard to be smart-ass in Chartres Cathedral.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.28,0:01:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.07,0:01:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hard in, I spoke one time in Westminster Abbey.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.56,0:01:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,As you walk through Westminster Abbey,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.98,0:01:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the great beings that have ever walked the planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.35,0:01:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,there's their tomb, there they lay there.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.35,0:02:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, as you walk across the floor,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.84,0:02:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a plate there that tells you who's under there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.18,0:02:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You think, my God, I shouldn't be stepping on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.20,0:02:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's Shakespeare and here's Napoleon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.41,0:02:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,All these great beings, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.84,0:02:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.18,0:02:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so the great cathedrals.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.87,0:02:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the value of religion is it recognizes the sacredness of beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.97,0:02:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The sacredness and the divinity of beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.93,0:02:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So, beauty is one of the fastest ways to the sense of the presence of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.05,0:02:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That music that we just played is 700,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.09,0:02:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's almost impossible to function on that level.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.56,0:02:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,In these lectures, I'm training myself to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.55,0:02:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hard to speak when you're weeping
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.88,0:02:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,because the beauty just wipes you out.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.59,0:03:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The sacredness of divinity then is acknowledged
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.22,0:03:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,through the self-sacrifice of the thousands and thousands of workmen.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.43,0:03:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of those cathedrals took over a thousand years,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.09,0:03:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,a thousand years, and they're still working on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.18,0:03:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,An entire lifetime is devoted to carving this one pulpit.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.19,0:03:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's in three dimensions.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.53,0:03:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,There's figures here and then figures...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.06,0:03:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Behind those figures, then figures behind them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.03,0:03:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,All done in hard wood.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.75,0:03:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,One entire lifetime just to carve this one gift to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.96,0:03:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.69,0:03:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The sense, the devotion of those whose devotion was so extreme
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.06,0:04:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,brings the energy of their devotion into your own inner experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.93,0:04:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and you get what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.09,0:04:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You get what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.65,0:04:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The worship and the recognition and the acknowledgement of the sacredness,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.53,0:04:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which is.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.81,0:04:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is divine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.46,0:04:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a road which anyone can take.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.14,0:04:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The appreciation for beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.75,0:04:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,A great aria in an opera can just wipe you out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.98,0:04:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to see Hansel and Gretel.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.50,0:04:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The children's chorus from Hansel and Gretel wakes you out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.94,0:04:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,La Boheme.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.06,0:04:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,There's an aria where he realizes that Mimi has just died,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.16,0:04:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and he screams Mimi.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.98,0:04:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You break out crying every time you hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.12,0:04:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I've seen that opera 10 or 12, 15 times.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.18,0:04:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Every time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.19,0:04:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The same.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.19,0:04:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The intensity of the love.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.63,0:05:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We experience the presence of God through love,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.04,0:05:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,through beauty,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.04,0:05:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,through that which is sacred.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.04,0:05:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So we are worshipful,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.80,0:05:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and we respect the sacredness of all of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.83,0:05:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We worship God when we turn the black beetle over
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.44,0:05:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,from his back onto his tummy,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.44,0:05:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,so he can walk away,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.44,0:05:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of living in the air with his legs wobbling in the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.68,0:05:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of that act, we worship God because
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.60,0:05:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,he's a god.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.60,0:05:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a god.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.82,0:05:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Life, so long as it exists in this form, is sacred.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.82,0:05:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And you realize the sacredness.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.82,0:05:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's an act of worship.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.99,0:05:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,All that we do that supports life
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.99,0:05:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,is a recognition of the respect for the sacredness of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.11,0:05:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's really all that's required.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.16,0:05:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it possible to transform the physical body into a spiritual body?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.16,0:06:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, oh, it means as Jesus did.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.60,0:06:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,My experience and understanding is,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.99,0:06:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,as one goes out of body,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.99,0:06:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,one's in the etheric body and the spiritual body.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.50,0:06:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,My guess would be that with the opening of the third eye,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.50,0:06:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the disciples were able to witness,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.79,0:06:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,usually when somebody goes out of physicality into the etheric realm,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.79,0:06:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't see them anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.79,0:06:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,My guess would be that with the opening of the third spiritual eye,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.79,0:06:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,they witnessed the spirit body of the Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.36,0:06:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to ask that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.36,0:06:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The disciples did have the opening of the third eye
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.76,0:06:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and witnessed the etheric body.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.87,0:06:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So they merely saw the spirit leaving the physicality.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.87,0:06:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't that the physical body is transformed into a spiritual body.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.13,0:07:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's that the spiritual body which inhabits the physical body
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.13,0:07:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,during its physical life leaves it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.97,0:07:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So it isn't like this physicality is transformed into the spirituality.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.97,0:07:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It just leaves it, is my understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.97,0:07:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Can kinesiology be used for future related questions?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.93,0:07:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.93,0:07:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It can't be used for the hypothetical.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.27,0:07:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And it can't be used for the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.27,0:07:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason is they're not real.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.48,0:07:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem with the hypothetical question is that
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.99,0:07:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,no answer is really possible
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.99,0:07:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,because it doesn't exist in reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.12,0:07:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What if mankind had four eyes?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.91,0:07:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Then what would happen to them?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.91,0:07:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no answer to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.91,0:07:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Hypothetically,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.91,0:07:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the hypothetical has no existence in reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.91,0:07:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a nonsense question.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.91,0:07:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of politics is that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.00,0:07:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,In which one quality is extracted
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.00,0:07:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and then that's supposed to be the most important thing
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.00,0:08:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,about your human being, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.00,0:08:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I got to do this for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.89,0:08:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Those people who talk from such ivory towers
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.89,0:08:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,should travel the slums of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.89,0:08:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how much high pollutants
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.01,0:08:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the political ideology appeals to the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.98,0:08:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,They're eating grubs to stay alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.43,0:08:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And you want them to die for the vote?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.43,0:08:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Vote for what?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.43,0:08:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,They're so far from that as a reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.97,0:08:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,To really exist from day to day is,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.76,0:08:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, rags tied together over branches.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.76,0:08:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And four families live in there
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.50,0:08:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,taking turns sleeping on the dirt floor
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.50,0:08:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,while they go about and eat actually more grubs than worms.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.50,0:08:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.83,0:08:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Covered with scabs
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.83,0:08:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and the bones all stick out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.52,0:08:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And by age five or six they're dead already.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.52,0:08:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Old age almost.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.52,0:08:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,In some parts of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.64,0:09:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember the people are all very small.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.64,0:09:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,There isn't much oxygen there anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.64,0:09:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,so it's a good thing they're small.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.64,0:09:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And the only way you can survive there
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.64,0:09:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is chewing cocoa leaf
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.64,0:09:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,because you can only work all day long
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.84,0:09:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,with nothing to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.84,0:09:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The cocoa leaf, it eliminates your hunger.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.87,0:09:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,If you had nothing to eat,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.87,0:09:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,you'd be stupid not to chew cocoa leaf, wouldn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.87,0:09:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.54,0:09:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So this way you can at least survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.87,0:09:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And this little old lady walked by,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.48,0:09:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,this little old lady with the ear pads
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.48,0:09:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,hanging down like this and all,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.48,0:09:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and they all pad about very quietly like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.48,0:09:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The descendants of the Incas,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.48,0:09:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,they live up in the mountains in Peru.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.48,0:09:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The government wants to get them down from there,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.48,0:09:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,but they don't want to come down
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.48,0:09:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,because they're smart.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.48,0:09:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.48,0:09:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Join the movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.48,0:09:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Join the big cities in the civilization.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.48,0:09:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This little old crone walks across there
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.50,0:09:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and I said to somebody,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.50,0:09:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,how old is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.79,0:09:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,She's 38.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.79,0:10:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,38, you're an old crone.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.79,0:10:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,By 40, you're dead of old age.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.47,0:10:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,This one vitamin tablet
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.78,0:10:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,would probably increase her lifespan by 10 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.98,0:10:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Tuberculosis is eating them up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.67,0:10:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't eat because of the cocoa leaf.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.67,0:10:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And if they do have some money,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.72,0:10:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,they spend it on beer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.10,0:10:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's a red feather hanging out of a shop
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.10,0:10:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,where you can buy beer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.23,0:10:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a different lifestyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.23,0:10:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And all that we consider important to them
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.23,0:10:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is so irrelevant,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.23,0:10:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,they don't even know what you're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.41,0:10:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You should all vote.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.41,0:10:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Vote for what?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.41,0:10:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,They're trying to get through
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.41,0:10:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,through till noon,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.41,0:10:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.41,0:10:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Our political system means absolutely nothing to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.41,0:10:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.41,0:10:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the downside of politics is
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.41,0:10:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,we're not aware of the consciousness level
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.41,0:10:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,of the people we're talking to.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.41,0:10:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,See, the egocentricity,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.58,0:11:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,we're so enamored of our own scheme of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.58,0:11:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, we're so superior.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.58,0:11:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Superior to what?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.84,0:11:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.22,0:11:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,when you're talking to people,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.22,0:11:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to be aware of their level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.22,0:11:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,so that you can speak meaningfully to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.91,0:11:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So, a lot of the diplomatic catastrophes of history
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.91,0:11:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,are because of the resumption.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.91,0:11:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That other people are like us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.91,0:11:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you folks, they are not like us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.91,0:11:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,They did not go to an Ivy League college.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.91,0:11:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,They did not play Marquis of Queensberry rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.91,0:11:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,They're street people.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.91,0:11:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,They made you sign a peace treaty with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.01,0:11:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You idiot, you turn around and they cut your throat.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.01,0:11:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the reason they got you to sign the peace treaty.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.50,0:11:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Because as you leave the table,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.50,0:11:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,they got you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.82,0:11:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Sucker.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.90,0:11:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So, those are the realities of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.90,0:11:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.09,0:11:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,it has to do with the sheep
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.09,0:11:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and the wolf in sheep's clothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.48,0:12:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The vulnerability of the spiritual seeker
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.48,0:12:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is that of naivete.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.48,0:12:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially in the beginning years
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.48,0:12:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,where you're enamored of the sudden discovery
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.48,0:12:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of the whole spiritual dimension.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.48,0:12:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's intriguing and it's exciting.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.47,0:12:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And in that space,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.47,0:12:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,one can go into denial
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.47,0:12:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,about the realities of this world
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.47,0:12:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and become a sitting duck.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.47,0:12:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's why I
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.47,0:12:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,always counsel these classes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.50,0:12:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be a plump little chicken.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.82,0:12:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they are out to get you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.84,0:12:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What is grace?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.84,0:12:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the function of grace?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.84,0:12:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Well,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.84,0:12:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,we said that the infinite totality
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.15,0:12:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,of all of creation then
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.73,0:12:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,radiates these energy fields.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.21,0:12:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,To get us out of good and bad
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.21,0:13:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and see things as gradations,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.39,0:13:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I made up this chart.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.39,0:13:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.55,0:13:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You could say up here is preferable
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.62,0:13:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is less preferable.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.62,0:13:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.20,0:13:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,People say, well, this, this,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.20,0:13:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the calibration of levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.51,0:13:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,could be used judgmentally.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.51,0:13:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.00,0:13:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It better be.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.63,0:13:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Is one thing better than another?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.12,0:13:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't that it's better than another.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.12,0:13:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,From what viewpoint?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.12,0:13:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,When it's cold, heat is preferable to chilly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.67,0:13:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,When it's hot, chilly is preferable to hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.67,0:13:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So, from what you choose then,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.72,0:13:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,everything gets rated.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.72,0:13:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,People say, well,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.23,0:14:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that's not fair
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.23,0:14:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that things are judged
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.23,0:14:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,one thing better than another.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.23,0:14:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you a fact about this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.51,0:14:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is better than something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.51,0:14:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And everything is worse than something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.25,0:14:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that's all in your head.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.75,0:14:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So, those who object to rating
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.90,0:14:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,people as good or bad or whatever,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.90,0:14:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,politically speaking, etc.,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.90,0:14:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,are playing a game of pretense,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.00,0:14:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of naivety.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.00,0:14:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, the wolf is hidden
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.00,0:14:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in the sheep's clothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.00,0:14:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that's denial of spiritual reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.00,0:14:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Some things are, frankly,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.20,0:14:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,a hell of a lot better than other things.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.19,0:14:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Not from an abstract point of view,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.52,0:14:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,no.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.52,0:14:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,From the abstract viewpoint,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.52,0:14:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you could say that all that exists is equal
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.52,0:14:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,by virtue of its existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.52,0:14:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But you don't see that
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.52,0:14:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,until you reach calibration level,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.95,0:15:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the top of the deck,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.95,0:15:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,until you reach a great...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.95,0:15:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,In the state of oneness,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.38,0:15:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,in the state of the allness of creation,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.38,0:15:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,you see that all things are equal.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.02,0:15:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But they are equal
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.22,0:15:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,in a different meaning of the term equal
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.22,0:15:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,than what is usually
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.60,0:15:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,used in common language.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.08,0:15:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't mean they are of different value.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.08,0:15:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It means each thing is
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.27,0:15:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,perfectly that which it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.60,0:15:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And beauty prevails throughout.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.60,0:15:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,A stick is equal to a diamond.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.46,0:15:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's of no difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.46,0:15:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, as you walk through the woods,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.36,0:15:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,this weed that stands there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.48,0:15:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you see what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.48,0:15:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,its architecture, its design,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.48,0:15:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.48,0:15:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It stands there in absolute perfection.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.19,0:15:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you don't call it weed anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.19,0:16:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You see it as an incredible sculpture.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.99,0:16:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The incredible sculpture of all that exists
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.99,0:16:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is equal to everything else that exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.24,0:16:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And I remember walking down the streets
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.24,0:16:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,of New York into the alley
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.62,0:16:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and struck by the incredible beauty of the alley.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.62,0:16:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,All the garbage cans and everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.62,0:16:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It was like
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.62,0:16:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,a French impressionistic painting almost.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.62,0:16:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,There was the garbage can
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.62,0:16:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,all dented over like that
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.62,0:16:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and the garbage hung out the side
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.62,0:16:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and the little mouse ran across
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.62,0:16:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and there was the banana peel.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.12,0:16:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there is a level in which you see
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.22,0:16:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the beauty and perfection of all that exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.22,0:16:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,When that begins to happen,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.22,0:16:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,you tell your friends
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.22,0:16:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're going to the retreat.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.22,0:16:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not safe on the streets.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.35,0:16:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You can get arrested.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.35,0:17:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Grace then is the presence,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.01,0:17:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the potentiality,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.01,0:17:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the presence of a very high energy
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.01,0:17:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,frequency and vibration
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.01,0:17:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,which through good fortune
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.44,0:17:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,one picks up in one's own aura
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.44,0:17:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,as an intentionality.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.07,0:17:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,As an intentionality
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.07,0:17:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,by agreement, by design, by subscription.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.94,0:17:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd go to see the Karmapa
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.60,0:17:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,because the Karmapa transmits a blessing
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.05,0:17:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,whether he does or doesn't is irrelevant
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.05,0:17:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,because your intention was
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.05,0:17:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to reach God through every available avenue
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.59,0:17:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and even if the Karmapa wasn't there
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.88,0:17:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,he is now by virtue of your intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.58,0:18:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Grace in a way is the opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.58,0:18:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to surrender to that which is intrinsic
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.58,0:18:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to salvation and enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.58,0:18:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It's walking down the street
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.79,0:18:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and suddenly you get
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.02,0:18:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,all you had to do was
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.02,0:18:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,start smiling at people
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.02,0:18:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and you've just transformed the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.02,0:18:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody can do that
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.31,0:18:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,walking down the streets
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.31,0:18:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,of New York City or Chicago.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.31,0:18:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You just start smiling at everybody
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.31,0:18:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and instantly everything happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.31,0:18:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.31,0:18:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It goes from this world to this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.41,0:18:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You did a smile at everybody
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.41,0:18:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and everybody goes, wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.41,0:18:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's the transformative opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.01,0:18:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,of a spiritual energy
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.01,0:18:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,which energizes options
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.07,0:18:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that would perhaps
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.07,0:18:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,not come to mind at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.07,0:18:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,In the last lecture we will talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.84,0:18:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,there's an important point
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.84,0:18:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in the evolution of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.84,0:19:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,where that grace is crucial.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.84,0:19:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Crucial.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.84,0:19:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,At that one ten-thousandth of a second
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.84,0:19:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that presence is crucial.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.54,0:19:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you really describe
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.70,0:19:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the physical sensations of the nervous system
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.70,0:19:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that you may feel
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.70,0:19:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,as one progresses in the spiritual path?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.89,0:19:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, they can be all kinds of
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.89,0:19:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,ailments.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.15,0:19:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,All kinds of ailments
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.15,0:19:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and weird and strange physical sensations.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.52,0:19:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,As one gets really quite advanced
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.52,0:19:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's because the nervous system
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.52,0:19:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,is being taxed by this spiritual energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.20,0:19:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a period of time
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.20,0:19:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's probably in the high five-hundreds.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.59,0:19:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What I'm thinking about now
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.59,0:19:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,is in the high five-hundreds.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.59,0:19:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It was coming on after six-hundreds.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.04,0:19:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It was coming on after seven-hundreds.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.92,0:20:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It starts at five-hundreds.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.64,0:20:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It starts at five-forty.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.02,0:20:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It starts at five-fifty.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.48,0:20:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It starts at five-eighty.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.67,0:20:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It starts at five-seventy-five.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.99,0:20:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Five-seventy, five-sixty-five.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.24,0:20:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.35,0:20:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,At energy level around five-sixty-five
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.35,0:20:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,which would be like saintliness
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.41,0:20:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,A Course in Miracles calibrates at six-hundreds.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.79,0:20:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,If you do it assiduously
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.79,0:20:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you get transported into that level.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.27,0:20:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And what is traditionally called the kundalini energy
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.40,0:20:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,a spiritual energy begins to flow of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.40,0:20:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's also facilitated by meditation.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.57,0:20:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if it is so.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.16,0:20:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The flow of the kundalini is also facilitated by meditation.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.59,0:21:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Through devotion, worship, spiritual intention
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.59,0:21:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and by meditation
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.75,0:21:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,this incredible energy begins to flow up your back.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.55,0:21:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.55,0:21:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's exquisite.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.55,0:21:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Better than an orgasm.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.55,0:21:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just beyond imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.00,0:21:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It flows as exquisite, joyful pleasure
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.00,0:21:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,up the back
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.00,0:21:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and you feel it flowing into the brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.41,0:21:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, you can direct where the energy goes
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.41,0:21:33.41,Default,,0,0,0,,by just sort of focusing your attention
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.41,0:21:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to the left side of the brain
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.41,0:21:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to teach the flow over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.41,0:21:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Focus on the right side of the brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.41,0:21:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It flows up your back
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.21,0:21:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and into the brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.36,0:21:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all I can explain.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.81,0:21:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, you witness this lady hobbling along.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.81,0:21:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,This energy flows out intensely
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.81,0:21:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's an exquisite sensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.81,0:21:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It flows out, flows in
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.81,0:21:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and you see the lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.81,0:22:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,She stops hobbling and she walks away.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.81,0:22:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It happens of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.72,0:22:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,One is merely the witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.72,0:22:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,This energy is what does it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.88,0:22:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy did it for years.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.88,0:22:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.56,0:22:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,irrecoverable, most hopelessly advanced,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.56,0:22:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,serious, psychotic, insane,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.56,0:22:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,degenerated, neurologic,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.56,0:22:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,bizarre creatures would be brought in
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.56,0:22:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,from all over the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.56,0:22:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,wrapped up in wet sheets,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.56,0:22:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,squirming on the ground
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.01,0:22:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.01,0:22:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.21,0:22:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And this energy would
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.21,0:22:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,connect with
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.17,0:22:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the self within the being there
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.17,0:22:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.61,0:22:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,you would feel the inner healing.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.39,0:22:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The inner being was
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.79,0:22:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,in the state of peace and grace.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.79,0:22:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened to the physicality
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.89,0:23:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,is irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.75,0:23:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I tell people
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.75,0:23:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,when you do the Course in Miracles,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.75,0:23:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,whether it cures you or something,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.75,0:23:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,if the Course is successful,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.75,0:23:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,it's irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.55,0:23:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Once the Course takes hold,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.55,0:23:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,what happens to the physicality
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.55,0:23:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is totally irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.24,0:23:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It may or may not heal itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.24,0:23:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,If it does, fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.55,0:23:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,If it doesn't, fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.55,0:23:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.39,0:23:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.04,0:23:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The kundalini energy is what...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.04,0:23:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I call it kundalini energy
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.04,0:23:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,because that's what
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.21,0:23:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Gopi Krishna wrote about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.21,0:23:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems like we just
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.59,0:23:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,determined it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.59,0:23:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's in the high 500s.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.66,0:23:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And it just is an exquisite state.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.66,0:23:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And in that state,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.66,0:23:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,you can only see and experience
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.66,0:23:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,love and beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.66,0:23:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing else exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.66,0:23:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The garbage cans are beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.98,0:23:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.98,0:24:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see the architectural,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.98,0:24:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,artistic beauty of the garbage cans.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.98,0:24:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see how every weed
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.98,0:24:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,is perfection.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.58,0:24:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And to this day,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.58,0:24:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,it makes no difference to me
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.58,0:24:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,whether a thing is a weed or a diamond.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.58,0:24:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither one.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.79,0:24:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Frankly, I don't need either one.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.79,0:24:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But they're equal.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.41,0:24:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,From that point on,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.41,0:24:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't need anything from this world
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.41,0:24:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,or from anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.41,0:24:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need anything from this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.01,0:24:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing that this world has
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.01,0:24:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that has any appeal to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.01,0:24:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.29,0:24:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,In the infinite presence,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.29,0:24:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no lack.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.29,0:24:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's no...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.29,0:24:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing you would want to reach out for.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.88,0:24:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing that you want or need.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.88,0:24:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,There is nothing temptable.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.31,0:24:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's why it's hard to understand
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.31,0:24:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,why some gurus have fallen.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.31,0:24:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Because in that state,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.76,0:24:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,there's nothing that can appeal to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.76,0:24:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So what was appealed to
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.79,0:25:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,must have been some remnant.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.79,0:25:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So that kundalini energy then pours in.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.32,0:25:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,In the beginning,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.64,0:25:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,there may be aches and pains.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.64,0:25:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's because the human nervous system
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.64,0:25:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is not made for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.64,0:25:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think we calibrated it
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.73,0:25:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,in a previous meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.73,0:25:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The human nervous system is made
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.73,0:25:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,for spiritual energies
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.73,0:25:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that calibrate up to 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.73,0:25:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And beyond that,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.59,0:25:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,you should go to other realms.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.59,0:25:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Go to other realms.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.59,0:25:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's designed for other realms.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.92,0:25:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So we said homo spiritus
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.92,0:25:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and the new emerging advance
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.10,0:25:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,of homo sapien
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.10,0:25:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,is in the process of developing
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.51,0:25:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,a stronger nervous system
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.51,0:25:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that can actually handle
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.51,0:25:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,more advanced spiritual energies.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.51,0:25:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, up to about 600
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.51,0:25:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is all that's comfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.48,0:26:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's comfortable up to around 700.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.54,0:26:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And then beyond that,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.54,0:26:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,it becomes painful.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.54,0:26:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Beyond that, there's,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.64,0:26:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,like the Buddha said,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.64,0:26:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you're beset by demons.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.64,0:26:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,There's aches and pains and fiery,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.25,0:26:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,fiery,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.38,0:26:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,fiery,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.38,0:26:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,fiery,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.38,0:26:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,fiery.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.38,0:26:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I can only liken it to
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.38,0:26:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,barbed wire
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.38,0:26:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that's running electricity through it
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.38,0:26:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's red hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.38,0:26:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And your whole nervous system
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.41,0:26:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes like that
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.41,0:26:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's agonizing.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.41,0:26:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And that means
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.41,0:26:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,there's something out
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.41,0:26:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and you've got to find out
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.41,0:26:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,what that is
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.66,0:26:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and you've got to clear that
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.66,0:26:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,through very intense puritano.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.66,0:26:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So the human nervous system, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.66,0:26:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,is made to handle energies
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.66,0:26:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,up to 600,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.66,0:26:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,up to 700, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.24,0:26:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And how should we pray?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.89,0:26:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we should pray
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.89,0:26:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,by the way we are in the world to respect and have reverence for all of life and the sanctity
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.96,0:27:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,of all that exists is the epitome of prayer to acknowledge god as the source and the presence
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.38,0:27:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of all existence in all of its expressions is the epitome of prayer people think of
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.00,0:27:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,prayers in terms of asking for favors oh god i want a mercedes-benz
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.82,0:27:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,she was something else wasn't she when she sang ball and chain the whole audience was just
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.38,0:27:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,suspended there's a long pause there in the music and everybody that sits on the edge of
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.66,0:27:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,their seats so they stand on their seats and then she finally she comes through with that note and
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.01,0:27:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,they all go oh to my mind prayer is not just a recitation see the intention of the recitation
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.93,0:27:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,is undoubtedly quite powerful just like prayer reels
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.76,0:28:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,it's the intention of the prayer reel that gives it its virgin power resist right so whether you
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.45,0:28:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,burn sticks uh walk back and forth around the squares and the floor of the cathedral
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.03,0:28:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever you do in the name of god for the sake of god is like karma yoga having been done
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.30,0:28:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,for the old lord and for the old lord do i thusly peel potatoes back in the floor so for the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.72,0:28:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,sake of god i'm going to take some pains of this body write thank you letters send christmas cards
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.31,0:28:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,pay my taxes whatever i do if i do it in the name of god in my because by doing that your
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.53,0:29:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,your understanding of the nature of god keeps expanding keeps expanding and that in itself
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.49,0:29:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,is a grace to see the opportunity and to follow that opportunity in itself is positive karma
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.49,0:29:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,is itself grace other people walk through great opportunities and don't see them they're blind
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.52,0:29:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and we can only feel sorry for them that they don't see the great opportunity there
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.72,0:29:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the difference between attachment and detachment well attachment is one of the biggest
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.56,0:29:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,problems in getting rid of the ego and probably the most important one if you can get rid of
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.56,0:29:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,attachments then you've saved yourself years of spiritual work
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.35,0:30:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,attachment itself is to some illusion to what you get out of something detachment is uh to say no to
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.04,0:30:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,it to negate it to refuse it attachment means to be hooked on it detachment would be indifference
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.31,0:30:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,detachment very often is the pathway of no asceticism which is also cool
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.25,0:30:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,it could be real happy with a cot a box candle and an apple a day
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.42,0:30:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,no money it's easy it's terrific you walk around free as a bird you walk into town somebody says
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.75,0:30:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,hey my mother just made some donuts you want one all right you walked somebody somebody said you
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.55,0:30:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,want to ride somewhere and i said yeah i was thinking going down just everything happens
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.50,0:31:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,mystically just wonderful don't need anything the downside of asceticism is that one can
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.88,0:31:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,get attached to asceticism you get off you get off on holiness and bone being bony
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.64,0:31:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,never taking a shower never washing your hair you can sit there cross-legged this bag of bones
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.25,0:31:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and maybe the you know the ascetics of indiana are the best example
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.92,0:31:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,i don't know that god's pleased by that or not probably not
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.79,0:31:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,i'm just kidding i've been into asceticism and uh you can get high on asceticism let's say you do
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.38,0:31:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't need anything it's fantastic you can walk out of the house without a
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.25,0:31:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,a nickel, nothing to eat, and everything gets provided day after day. It just happens. The
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.48,0:32:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,miraculous becomes constant. Of course, when you're detached, you're not attached to the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.64,0:32:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,survival of life and the body, which can be annoying to your family. They want you to
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.63,0:32:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,take care of it and eat and all kinds of strange things, get haircuts, take their medicine,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.79,0:32:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,see the doctor. It's a drag. Anyway, anybody forces you to take all these measures, you
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.48,0:32:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,do it because you love them. Frankly, that's why you do it. Left to your own, you wouldn't
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.34,0:32:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,bother. Left to my own, I wouldn't bother eating. I mean, what would you bother eating
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.26,0:32:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,for? I used to not eat for long periods of time, and it would only dawn on me. I hadn't
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.78,0:32:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,eaten all week.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.53,0:32:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's like you didn't
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.82,0:32:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,need food. What do you want food
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.89,0:32:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,for? The perfect state is
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.25,0:32:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,neither attraction nor aversion.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.36,0:33:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither attachment nor
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.02,0:33:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,detachment necessarily,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.95,0:33:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,but non-attachment.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.70,0:33:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So the present
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.79,0:33:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,state is
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.85,0:33:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,to be not attached. You don't have an aversion
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.06,0:33:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,nor do you have an attraction.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.23,0:33:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And if there's something for
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.84,0:33:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,dinner, that's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.80,0:33:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And if there isn't something for dinner, that's also
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.78,0:33:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,great, because you're not attached
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.00,0:33:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,one way or the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.25,0:33:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Non-attachment. It means you're not run
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.50,0:33:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,by it anymore. You're not run by
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.59,0:33:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,it. And tapas,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.74,0:33:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the traditional way of
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.31,0:33:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,P-A-P-A-S, is
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.40,0:33:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the practice of non-attachment to
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.44,0:33:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,things. If you always have to have
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.55,0:33:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,your dinner at 5.30,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.14,0:33:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,then you stop doing that until you get over
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.96,0:33:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that yin that it's got to be on the table at
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.81,0:33:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,5.30 or your whole life's
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.81,0:33:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,going to be upset.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.08,0:34:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,When you say
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.81,0:34:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,divine intervention is needed,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.61,0:34:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,to save us, I hear divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.72,0:34:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,as something other.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.16,0:34:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But there is no other to save
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.23,0:34:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,us from what? Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.36,0:34:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Divine intervention
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.59,0:34:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,is just a style of speech.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.48,0:34:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It means, out of good
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.82,0:34:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,karma, out of the karma which may
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.69,0:34:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,arise out of the good karma of this instant,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.40,0:34:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I ask God to help me.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.84,0:34:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Came out of what must be
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.96,0:34:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,horrific negative karma, to end
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.32,0:34:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,up in the depths of hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.63,0:34:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps in that instant was all the karma
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.51,0:34:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,by grace.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.34,0:34:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it requires
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.69,0:34:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,with the one act,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.19,0:34:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,from here to there. Heaven and hell are a
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.63,0:34:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,tenth of an inch apart, says Zen.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.13,0:35:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.69,0:35:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.61,0:35:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Hitting bottom may be the
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.67,0:35:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,fastest way to heaven. That's why
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.71,0:35:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,intervening and
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.65,0:35:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,being an enabler
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.42,0:35:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is interfering with the other person's
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.65,0:35:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,karmic lesson. You keep
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.80,0:35:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,running in and saving them and hauling them
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.86,0:35:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,off to the hospital and
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.98,0:35:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,give me a break. The mother used to
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.07,0:35:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,call me up. The family called me up.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.07,0:35:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to stop drinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.15,0:35:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, you know what to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.13,0:35:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Buy him a case of whiskey and put him
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.01,0:35:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in a hotel room. Call me back
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.84,0:35:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,when he's done. Right. That's the
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.07,0:35:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,best way to help this guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.71,0:35:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And when he runs out of a case of whiskey, buy him
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.65,0:35:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,another case of whiskey. Pretty soon
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.44,0:35:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the voices are after me, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.32,0:35:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Help, help. Okay, Junior.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.48,0:35:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we'll take you to the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.63,0:35:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, when you're not ready,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.19,0:35:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,you're not ready, folks. You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.61,0:35:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.32,0:35:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.44,0:35:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true. Buy him a case of whiskey and leave him
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.42,0:36:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,be. You know, why are you messing with this guy
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.59,0:36:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and interfering with his karma?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.42,0:36:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because the good karma
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.53,0:36:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,only comes when he surrenders to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.15,0:36:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,When he says, God, I've gone
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.42,0:36:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,as far as I can go.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.30,0:36:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,If there is a God, I ask him to help me.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.69,0:36:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That stops the
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.67,0:36:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,insanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.98,0:36:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,When you admit that you, of your own
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.30,0:36:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,nature, you, your little lone
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.48,0:36:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,ego in the middle of the universe, can't
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.28,0:36:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,hack it, can't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.17,0:36:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That's truth. That's integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.23,0:36:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.55,0:36:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you cross over the line
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.40,0:36:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,of integrity. I, myself,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.86,0:36:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot do it. No.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.80,0:36:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Only by
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.46,0:36:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,grace. And you realize
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.03,0:36:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that you've been insane.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.19,0:36:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And you ask God to help
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.30,0:36:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you and you surrender your life to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.78,0:36:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,From that moment on, your
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.26,0:36:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,life is transformed. And this
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.82,0:36:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,room is full of people whose lives have been
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.28,0:36:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,transformed in just
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.59,0:36:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.28,0:36:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the grace, then, is that that is
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.34,0:37:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,present and available
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.55,0:37:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.67,0:37:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Every moment. It doesn't mean that it's
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.76,0:37:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,going to be answered at every moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.63,0:37:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You can pray up a storm for 20 years
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.40,0:37:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and nothing happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.17,0:37:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And you say, the heck with prayer. I give it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.59,0:37:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And at that instant...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.90,0:37:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you realize you've been
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.63,0:37:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to control God with prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.69,0:37:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You've been trying to control
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.50,0:37:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,him, control. That you weren't
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.40,0:37:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,really surrendering. Because if you totally
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.19,0:37:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,surrender to God, it doesn't matter whether the
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.26,0:37:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Romantism continues or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.71,0:37:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, the ailments that you have are really,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.61,0:37:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,really irrelevant, you know, unless
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.07,0:37:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,they interfere with functioning. Today, I had to
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.00,0:37:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,speak, and all week long, I had some terrible
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.86,0:37:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,virus. Terrible virus.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.25,0:37:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.19,0:37:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,well, either you speak Saturday or you don't speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.11,0:37:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't speak, you don't speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.11,0:37:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't speak,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.11,0:37:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,you won't say anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.82,0:38:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,In which case, we'll just sit together and pray, maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.13,0:38:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,This asks
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.71,0:38:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,about beings below the 200s.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.25,0:38:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We said, this world seems,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.46,0:38:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,from my personal viewpoint,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.73,0:38:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,in fact, you can use the term personal
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.25,0:38:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,in its usual vernacular,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.09,0:38:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the world seems
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.73,0:38:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,purgatorial in design.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.09,0:38:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because you
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.36,0:38:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,go from the very lowest
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.75,0:38:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,element, the reptile,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.28,0:38:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the great dinosaurs
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.19,0:38:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,at 70 lived by
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.61,0:38:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,ravaging and slashing and killing.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.63,0:38:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,They live
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.98,0:38:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,solely by the death of others.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.55,0:38:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The dinosaur lives
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.38,0:38:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,only,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.84,0:38:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,only by killing you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.76,0:38:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Its sole purpose is to kill
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.53,0:38:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you, because you are food.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.44,0:38:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,That's about as low as you can get, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.67,0:38:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess worse would be
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.78,0:38:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,kill you and not eat you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.67,0:38:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,At least they eat you.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.15,0:39:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That's starting
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.96,0:39:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,somewhere, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.50,0:39:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, we get to
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.78,0:39:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,all we can say is
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.26,0:39:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that consciousness evolved
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.94,0:39:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,on this planet. It seemed
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.36,0:39:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to come up from,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.61,0:39:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and there are still beings
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.76,0:39:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,at the bottom of the sea
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.11,0:39:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,who are really
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.94,0:39:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,awesomely awesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.76,0:39:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And we see that it evolved
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.30,0:39:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,over great eons of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.94,0:39:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,millions of years,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.23,0:39:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,400 million years,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.07,0:39:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,for instance.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.42,0:39:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we see consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.86,0:39:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,slowly come up to where
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.15,0:39:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,it has been.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.88,0:39:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And we see that life
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.42,0:39:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,on this earth has been
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.65,0:39:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,a reflection.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.28,0:39:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So life, we said
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.78,0:39:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that the world of form
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.82,0:39:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,is the consequence
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.38,0:39:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which is held
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.21,0:39:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,in consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.84,0:39:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a world of effects.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.90,0:40:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a world of causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.71,0:40:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a world of effects
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.09,0:40:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,in which that which is held
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.53,0:40:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,in consciousness creates this,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.15,0:40:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and then this, and then this,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.15,0:40:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and then this.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.13,0:40:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you walk down the path,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.69,0:40:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you think it's sequential.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.59,0:40:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not sequential.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.80,0:40:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's continuous.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.36,0:40:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Creation is continuous.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.98,0:40:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,All things are constantly
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.15,0:40:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the result of an ongoing,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.11,0:40:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,ongoing creation
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.30,0:40:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,which is continuous.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.17,0:40:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Creation to be creation
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.15,0:40:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot start and stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.00,0:40:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is outside of time
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.44,0:40:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,has no capacity
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.71,0:40:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to start and stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.71,0:40:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Thusly, everything that is happening
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.38,0:40:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is the continuous expression
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.44,0:40:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,of creation,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.36,0:40:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the divinity,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.26,0:40:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the infinite power of God,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.13,0:40:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,bringing potentiality
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.67,0:40:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,into manifestation.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.90,0:40:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.86,0:41:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,as it evolved then,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.01,0:41:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,reached 190,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.59,0:41:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,for centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.48,0:41:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it's at 207,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.25,0:41:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and life has changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.86,0:41:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Discuss the Trinity,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.01,0:41:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,God's Son and Holy Spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.57,0:41:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That's interesting
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.42,0:41:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,because it caused the great division
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.30,0:41:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Christian Church,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.82,0:41:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the Eastern and the Western,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.36,0:41:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Constantinople and Rome,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.90,0:41:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,split over this whole concept.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.84,0:41:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And it has a theological name,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.86,0:41:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget what the argument is about.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.78,0:41:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,There's three different ways
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.01,0:41:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,of looking at things.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.26,0:41:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Because reality is a total,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.01,0:41:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,complete oneness,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.46,0:41:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,it cannot have a triune quality.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.44,0:41:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It can have a triune quality
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.03,0:41:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,from a certain perception,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.80,0:41:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,from a certain level of perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.28,0:41:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We see the triune quality
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.01,0:41:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,of divinity in the world's religions.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.28,0:41:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Brahma, Vishnu, Shiva,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.82,0:42:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,we see it in Christianity,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.69,0:42:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Father, God, the Son,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.36,0:42:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and God, the Holy Spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.61,0:42:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,God, the Holy Spirit,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.69,0:42:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and God, the Holy Spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.78,0:42:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,God, the Holy Spirit,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.94,0:42:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,When we say God, the Son,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.25,0:42:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,we're talking about divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.71,0:42:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,as it is expressed in form.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.23,0:42:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That divinity can express itself
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.21,0:42:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,through the human,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.90,0:42:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,through the great avatar.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.13,0:42:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We see that God is invisible
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.19,0:42:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to ordinary perception
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.40,0:42:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,as that which is transcendent.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.84,0:42:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,God is imminent then
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.36,0:42:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,within the avatar.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.67,0:42:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And what makes it imminent
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.78,0:42:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,is the Holy Spirit,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.88,0:42:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.61,0:42:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Holy Spirit would be like
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.57,0:42:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the radiance of God,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.21,0:42:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy field of God,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.36,0:42:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,which may then express itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.36,0:42:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,at least to a limited degree,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.86,0:42:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,within a physicality.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.84,0:42:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the invisible context.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.15,0:42:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,When we pray,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.86,0:42:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what we're referring to,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.84,0:43:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is we've changed
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.32,0:43:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the quantum potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.48,0:43:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,How does prayer work?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.30,0:43:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It changes the quantum potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.07,0:43:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,If you follow quantum mechanics,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.01,0:43:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,you realize that merely to witness
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.94,0:43:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,or observe a thing already
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.69,0:43:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,changes it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.80,0:43:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The past and the present
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.17,0:43:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and the future change.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.82,0:43:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The future now becomes the past,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.65,0:43:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and the past becomes the future, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.03,0:43:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you're out of linearity.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.17,0:43:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The human mind really can't conceive,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.34,0:43:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't really understand quantum mechanics.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.96,0:43:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Because only the spiritually evolved person
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.21,0:43:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,gets what it's saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.09,0:43:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That which you are
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.80,0:43:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,is influenced by the quantum mechanics.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.78,0:43:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That which you are is influenced
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.30,0:43:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,by influencing everything else that exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.13,0:43:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,By the virtue of that which you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.80,0:43:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you change the charge and the potentiality,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.59,0:44:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore the likelihood
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.34,0:44:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,of a thing coming into actuality
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.34,0:44:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and form,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.51,0:44:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,depending on local conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.76,0:44:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Every one of us then,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.21,0:44:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,by their style of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.61,0:44:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,by their devotion,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.73,0:44:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,by their witness to the acknowledgement
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.50,0:44:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,of the sacredness of all of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.23,0:44:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,lifts the consciousness of all of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.92,0:44:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,All of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.90,0:44:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,All of mankind is benefited.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.90,0:44:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing goes unobserved.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.25,0:44:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a hair on your head
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.63,0:44:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,shall be missed.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.48,0:44:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That turned out to be accurate.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.09,0:44:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember when I first discovered
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.75,0:44:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the capacity of kinesiology
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.82,0:44:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,to tell truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.59,0:44:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And I realized that everything that ever existed
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.51,0:44:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is registered forever
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.88,0:44:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,in the field of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.15,0:44:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, whoa.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.07,0:44:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Every hair on your head
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.78,0:44:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,shall be counted.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.92,0:44:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa. It's the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.67,0:44:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a fact. Every squirrel that falls,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.25,0:44:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,is noted.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.73,0:45:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Intrinsic divinitive existence
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.48,0:45:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,is equal in all.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.46,0:45:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Is equal in all.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.17,0:45:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Witnessed, acknowledged by all.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.65,0:45:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,When we say God imminent,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.28,0:45:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,God transcendent,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.23,0:45:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,when we talk about Trinity,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.59,0:45:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,God, Son, Holy Spirit,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.78,0:45:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,those are only linguistic,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.36,0:45:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,conceptual,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.48,0:45:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,rationalistic positionalities
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.61,0:45:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,from which to approach the subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.05,0:45:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,When you read,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.73,0:45:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,theology, realize
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.94,0:45:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,what a difficult job that is
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.13,0:45:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,to try to describe the non-linear
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.01,0:45:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,in terms that are linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.46,0:45:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,To describe that which is indefinable.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.76,0:45:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see how you can define the indefinable.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.13,0:45:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what theology is about.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.65,0:45:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Class, we will define the indefinable.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.11,0:45:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.92,0:45:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see the difficulty.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.32,0:45:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,However, you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.71,0:45:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you can also see the
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.40,0:46:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,devotion in that.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.61,0:46:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Because, many of the great intellectual,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.65,0:46:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual teachers of history,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.05,0:46:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,in the religious thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.71,0:46:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,were very learned.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.59,0:46:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,They were doctors of theology.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.59,0:46:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Their devotion was to the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.17,0:46:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and it took the form of a seeking truth
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.17,0:46:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,through the intellect and reason and logic.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.65,0:46:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So, one can still be respectful of the devotion
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.63,0:46:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,behind the endeavor to try to reach,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.40,0:46:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.78,0:46:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,if you read about the books,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.09,0:46:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, it'll discuss whether God is imminent or transcendent.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.98,0:46:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this is an artifact of mentation.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.55,0:46:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It couldn't possibly be either or.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.15,0:46:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,God being the essence of all that exists,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.67,0:46:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the allness throughout and beyond all time,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.76,0:46:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,could hardly be limited,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.94,0:46:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,could hardly be divided into transcendent,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.78,0:47:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,which is out there,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.78,0:47:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and imminent, which is in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.13,0:47:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are obviously just artifacts of human mentation.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.09,0:47:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We've sort of touched upon prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.55,0:47:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We need the Newtonian versus the,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.55,0:47:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to put it within conceptual basis,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.19,0:47:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to spend much time at this,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.19,0:47:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's worth,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.36,0:47:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,for the doubting Thomas,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.36,0:47:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,there are people who are stuck in their intellect,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.36,0:47:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and victims of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.42,0:47:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't get out of my brain, dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.80,0:47:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't get out of logic, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.80,0:47:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.44,0:47:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But God in his infinite mercy knows that,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.88,0:47:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that you are stuck in your head.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.88,0:47:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,For those who are stuck in their head then,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.69,0:47:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,it's okay to be spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.84,0:48:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,because we now have a scientific explanation
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.84,0:48:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,for the reality of the spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.42,0:48:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the Newtonian paradigm of reality on the left,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.25,0:48:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,in which things are discrete, orderly, logical,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.25,0:48:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,definable, measurable,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.25,0:48:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's what the material reductionist,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.25,0:48:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the hardcore scientist says is what's real.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.25,0:48:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't measure it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.25,0:48:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't weigh it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.25,0:48:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't locate it in time and space.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.25,0:48:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not real.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.25,0:48:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That's sort of taking great liberties with the word real.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.76,0:48:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, it's really missing what real is about,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.07,0:48:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,but anyway, that's beside the point.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.28,0:48:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is the world that we presume to be reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.28,0:48:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,except that actually we don't
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.28,0:48:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,because nobody lives on that level.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.30,0:48:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We entertain ourselves with that level,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.30,0:48:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,but we all know we live on the experiential,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.30,0:48:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,either like the plum pudding or you don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.30,0:48:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Got too much this in it or too much that.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.46,0:48:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The liver is fried too hard
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.46,0:49:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's tough as leather or it isn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.46,0:49:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.92,0:49:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is where we live over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.92,0:49:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We live in the infinite quantum potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.92,0:49:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, as we get smaller and smaller
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.98,0:49:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,below the atom, below the sub-particles,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.98,0:49:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,sub-particle physics,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.98,0:49:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,we get to like potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.40,0:49:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Like potential energies that are so minute
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.40,0:49:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that they cannot be measured.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.00,0:49:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And we enter a different realm.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.00,0:49:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We enter a different realm.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.73,0:49:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We enter the world where we live.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.73,0:49:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Where we live is in spirituality.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.73,0:49:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,People say, I don't believe in spirituality.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.92,0:49:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Idiot, you live there all day long.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.92,0:49:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, what just said you don't live in spirituality
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.92,0:49:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is what spirituality is.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.01,0:49:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a subjective conclusion
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.01,0:49:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and how did that come about?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.01,0:49:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the totality of all one's thinkingness
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.01,0:50:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout all of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.01,0:50:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,one's karmic inheritance
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.01,0:50:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and what your consciousness level is now
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.23,0:50:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that leads you to feel that way within yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.23,0:50:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that gives it that sense of truth
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.23,0:50:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that you say this is so highly complex,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.23,0:50:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,completely non-linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.23,0:50:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So where we live is really disorderly.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.96,0:50:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything can happen within your experiential life.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.96,0:50:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You can go to your favorite opera
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.96,0:50:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and be disappointed instead of ecstatic.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.96,0:50:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You can buy your best ice cream
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.96,0:50:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that you've always liked your whole life
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.96,0:50:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and you decide it's disgusting.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.96,0:50:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't really predict what's going to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.09,0:50:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's creative. It's free.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.09,0:50:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's imaginative. It's progressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.09,0:50:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's diffuse. It's non-local.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.67,0:50:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's experiential.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.96,0:50:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's expansive.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.96,0:50:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the context out of which we live.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.96,0:50:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the subjective state.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.25,0:50:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And at all times we're really poised
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.25,0:50:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,for the next instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.28,0:51:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The context of our life then is unlimited.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.28,0:51:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,At every moment we're poised for the next instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.28,0:51:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Without even being conscious and aware that we're poised,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.28,0:51:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,at every instant everybody here is ready to jump!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.57,0:51:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That jumping-ness can happen out of non-jumping-ness.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.32,0:51:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing said jump in the head.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.32,0:51:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It just jumped. See?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.55,0:51:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So everything is happening spontaneously
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.55,0:51:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,as an expression of the essence of...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.61,0:51:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the reality of that which it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.61,0:51:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,This entire lecture was prepared exactly
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.11,0:51:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,one ten-thousandth of a second ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.26,0:51:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Jump wasn't in it. You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.98,0:51:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's some things about the downside of social life.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.30,0:51:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The downside of social life.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.23,0:52:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,There are those things which are preferable
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.23,0:52:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and those things which are not preferable.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.23,0:52:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,See, if we can get beyond good and evil,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.30,0:52:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,we can say there's the things that we want
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.36,0:52:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and we call them good.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.36,0:52:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's the things we don't want
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.36,0:52:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and we call them bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.26,0:52:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Now here we've got, which we had before
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.11,0:52:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,but we didn't talk about.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.30,0:52:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,See, good and bad, just like talking about the Trinity,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.30,0:52:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,depends on where you want to start from.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.30,0:52:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And what you're talking about is the perception
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.30,0:52:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and what you're talking about is the point
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.30,0:52:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,from which you're approaching the subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.96,0:52:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If you desire it, you say it's good,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.96,0:52:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you don't desire it, you say it's bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.96,0:52:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So the things that we consider tragic about society,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.15,0:52:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,about human life,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.15,0:52:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,war and the downside of the judiciary system,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.15,0:53:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,yes, there is a downside to it,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.51,0:53:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,are because we don't want those things.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.57,0:53:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So we choose what we want
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.71,0:53:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and we repel that which we don't want.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.71,0:53:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,In the highest state, they're all the same,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.71,0:53:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,as we said.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.71,0:53:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,War and peace, it's all the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.71,0:53:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether you all go off with an atomic bomb, bang,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.71,0:53:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,or you slowly strangle to death from old age,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.71,0:53:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,what's the difference?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.71,0:53:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you're going to leave here quick and easy
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.07,0:53:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,or slow and horrible, you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.42,0:53:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Leaving is leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.42,0:53:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And whatever karmic merit there is
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.42,0:53:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and the style that's chosen,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.03,0:53:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,but that's a very advanced state.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.03,0:53:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But there is a certain level at which you can see
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.23,0:53:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that it really doesn't matter
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.32,0:53:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,because this being a karmic theater,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.32,0:53:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,this being a theater of great opportunity,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.32,0:53:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,then we can choose that which we choose
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.32,0:54:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and not choose that which we mean to avoid.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.32,0:54:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I myself wouldn't want the karma
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.55,0:54:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,of being a judge in a murder case.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.55,0:54:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,No, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.55,0:54:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't want the karma
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.30,0:54:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,of being the one that says,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.30,0:54:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,this person dies or doesn't die or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.67,0:54:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So I think the difficulty with leading a moral
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.03,0:54:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,or an ethical or spiritual life in the West,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.90,0:54:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Western world,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.90,0:54:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,is the lack of the understanding of karma,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.90,0:54:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the lack of the understanding of the nature of God,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.23,0:54:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that everything and every moment
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.23,0:54:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,determines one's spiritual destiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.46,0:54:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That everything, every moment
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.46,0:54:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,is an act that is witnessed by the entire universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.46,0:54:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The entire universe witnesses every single act
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.46,0:54:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and every single choice
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.46,0:54:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and records it forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.98,0:55:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, in the demonstrations we do of kinesiology
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.36,0:55:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and the potentiality of it
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.36,0:55:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,as a research tool,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.67,0:55:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,we go back in history,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.67,0:55:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,any human being that ever lived,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.67,0:55:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,what they thought or felt,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.67,0:55:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,what they did,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.67,0:55:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,why they made the choice,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.67,0:55:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing is hidden.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.28,0:55:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is hidden.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.48,0:55:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So from the infinite eye of the divine,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.48,0:55:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing is hidden.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.90,0:55:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.90,0:55:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,neither does it need to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.44,0:55:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the blessing.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.44,0:55:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll break for lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.44,0:55:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll see you again later.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.44,0:57:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,About an hour or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.40,0:57:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.36,0:57:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Be able to function
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.36,0:57:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,in the presence of the beauty of God
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.36,0:57:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,is difficult and takes practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.03,0:57:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And by Lecture 11,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.03,0:57:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I've made good progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.86,0:58:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It used to be
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.86,0:58:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I could either deal with the music
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.86,0:58:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,or talk, but not both.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.86,0:58:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,How to not be wiped out by it?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.86,0:58:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Question number one.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.46,0:58:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it the mind-boggler of all time?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.46,0:58:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,How does one truly find themself?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.46,0:58:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's a snap, folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.44,0:58:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You just realize you're the infinite allness
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.44,0:58:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,of all existence beyond all time and expression.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.44,0:58:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,There you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.44,0:58:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't take long, did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.76,0:58:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,After many lifetimes,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.07,0:58:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I got a neat letter from somebody the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.32,0:58:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,He says,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.32,0:58:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been meditating for 30 years,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.17,0:58:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and suddenly,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.71,0:59:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,boom.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.09,0:59:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,How neat.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.09,0:59:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,There's questions about prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.59,0:59:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There's questions about meditation.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.88,0:59:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Wonderful questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.88,0:59:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He said that the ultimate form of prayer
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.21,0:59:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,is the way in which you conceptualize,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.55,0:59:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the way in which you contextualize
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.55,0:59:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,your own existence from instant to instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.55,0:59:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Meditation and prayer
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.32,0:59:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is more like a mudra
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.32,0:59:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,than a recitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.03,0:59:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's more like a posture
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.80,0:59:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,in which you pose your existence
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.80,0:59:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in the context of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.00,0:59:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the style in which you are
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.51,1:00:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,out of the awareness of the presence of God
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.69,1:00:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and once surrendered to be of service to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.63,1:00:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That sanctifies all actions.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.11,1:00:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It is by your dedication of yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.57,1:00:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to that intention
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.86,1:00:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that you sanctify all your actions.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.86,1:00:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.61,1:00:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the last thing,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.61,1:00:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the last thing that I want to do
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.61,1:00:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is ask you a question
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.61,1:00:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that I must ask.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.61,1:00:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it from you
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.03,1:00:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to do with your action?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:47.03,1:00:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What is your action?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.61,1:00:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have an action?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.61,1:00:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the action you do
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.07,1:00:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,to help you relax?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.07,1:00:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.25,1:00:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.25,1:00:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm trying to give you
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.59,1:00:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,a few different answers.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.59,1:01:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a strange question.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.59,1:01:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It really is.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.59,1:01:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.59,1:01:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,if it's the same or a different answer.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.86,1:01:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It really is.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.86,1:01:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,If I do something wrong,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.86,1:01:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that person
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.86,1:01:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a sense of wholesomeness about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.92,1:01:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's made by a machine, there's certain brands of bread
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.17,1:01:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that you could blindfold me,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.40,1:01:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and the minute you put it in your mouth, it tastes dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.44,1:01:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Twinkies. I'm very disappointed in Twinkies.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.88,1:01:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, Twinkies came to mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.07,1:01:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was a kid, you'd go out for, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.23,1:01:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,your mom would put a Twinkie in there,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.73,1:01:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and at lunch you'd have your Twinkie,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.80,1:01:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and you'd squeeze that banana-flavored goodness out of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.92,1:01:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Twinkies were great.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.75,1:01:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,One day, out of madness, I decided to buy a Twinkie for old-time's sake.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.84,1:01:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, it was deader than a mackerel.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.80,1:01:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it is not the same Twinkie that I grew up with.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.38,1:01:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Food that is blessed carries a different energy,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.11,1:02:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,so the human energy does something to the energy of the food itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.03,1:02:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So witness the mother who lovingly makes the chicken soup.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.21,1:02:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It actually does cure your cold.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.96,1:02:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And the tea that's made it,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.76,1:02:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and the tea that's made it home has cured this cold.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.28,1:02:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because of the energy of love within it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.94,1:02:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So we transform everything that we touch.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.15,1:02:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that people who have a green thumb, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.63,1:02:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,it's like they see the sacredness of beauty.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.90,1:02:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They dedicate their life to the cultivation of beauty for its own sake.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.13,1:02:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We sanctify that which we do then by the dedication of our life
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.51,1:02:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to be conscious that all one's actions are in the presence of God
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.80,1:02:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and that every action is in the presence of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.55,1:02:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And that every action affects all of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.73,1:02:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So your life no longer is trivial.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.15,1:02:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Your life is no longer trivial.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.00,1:02:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that you're out on a river fishing,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.38,1:03:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,as you look over and you appreciate the beauty of that river and the surroundings,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.38,1:03:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,your appreciation of that beauty is radiating out and lifting all of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.80,1:03:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So even as you sit in the rowboat thinking that you're doing nothing,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.53,1:03:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,your acknowledgement of the beauty of creation itself
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.44,1:03:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is an act of love.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.23,1:03:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an act of sanctifying all of life
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.17,1:03:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and affirming its value and increasing its value.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.38,1:03:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's how the consciousness level of mankind evolves
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.63,1:03:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is because those who are more conscious tend to lift all of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.73,1:03:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We said that the top of the levels of consciousness are numerically small,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.34,1:03:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,but their power outweighs...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.94,1:03:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,but their power outweighs all the rest of the population.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.17,1:04:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,One person who dedicates themself to life
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.92,1:04:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and sees the sacredness of all of life
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.23,1:04:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and thereby sanctifies all of life as they go about the day
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.80,1:04:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is lifting the consciousness of thousands of other people.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.92,1:04:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Somewhere in Biatra, some little kid is laying there,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.21,1:04:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,slowly dying of starvation and AIDS.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.15,1:04:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And out of his hopelessness and grief and apathy,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.05,1:04:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly there's a little spark of hope.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.53,1:04:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And death is okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.19,1:04:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did that come from?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.80,1:04:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It came from the fisherman sitting there appreciating the beauty.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.09,1:04:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, because the context of life is non-linear,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.21,1:04:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,so in the infinite quantum potentiality,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.38,1:04:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,every intention on your part alters the context for everyone.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.38,1:04:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Every hair on your head is counted.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.28,1:05:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Every moment of your life contributes this way
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.03,1:05:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,or it pulls it down this way.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.90,1:05:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The number of people who are living in this world,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.75,1:05:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the number of people who are living in this world,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.92,1:05:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the number of people who calibrate on the high levels
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.78,1:05:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,has increased since 1980, 1990, whatever it was,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.01,1:05:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,1990s when I did it, early 1990s.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.59,1:05:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And the calibration of the level of all of mankind is going up.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.30,1:05:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And we see, as we said, at 207, integrity no longer,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.34,1:05:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,people don't wink at it anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.03,1:05:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,They put it on the front cover of Fortune magazine.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.71,1:05:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Integrity is being called for by everyone.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.09,1:05:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So what do you say to God
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.44,1:05:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,when you pray?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.01,1:05:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what other people say to God when they pray.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.92,1:05:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I could use a few more bucks, God.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.11,1:05:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Rent's due next week.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.34,1:05:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I'm sure God doesn't take offense at that.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.28,1:06:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's really a serious question of how does one pray.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.92,1:06:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The most effective prayer, as far as I know, is non-verbal.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.86,1:06:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It is to position oneself.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.13,1:06:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what a mudra is?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.50,1:06:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,A mudra is...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.82,1:06:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, divine statues.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.07,1:06:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,A mudra is this.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.40,1:06:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Mudra is the dance of Shiva.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.55,1:06:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Mudra is a posture.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.90,1:06:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,A mudra is blessing.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.73,1:06:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Mudra is...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.44,1:06:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's one's...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.59,1:06:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The way you position your existence vis-a-vis divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.63,1:06:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like there's an...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.53,1:06:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,If you picture an invisible self,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.67,1:06:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,what would be the posture of your invisible self?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.75,1:06:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.05,1:06:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.44,1:06:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,in the presence of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.67,1:07:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.05,1:07:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's ask.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.15,1:07:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to ask about that
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.15,1:07:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,form of prayer resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.59,1:07:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's more effective than
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.09,1:07:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,verbalization resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.23,1:07:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,More effective than verbalization.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.36,1:07:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a supplication of your spirit
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.00,1:07:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,to God's will.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.69,1:07:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The surrender to God's will
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.48,1:07:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is a form of prayer.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.88,1:07:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,When you say,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.01,1:07:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,for what reason I don't know, Lord,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.67,1:07:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,but I, whatever,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.07,1:07:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in thy name, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.01,1:07:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's the undoing of some bad karma,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.00,1:07:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,you might say,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.05,1:07:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what the reason for this suffering is,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.71,1:07:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,but I dedicate it for, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.90,1:07:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the undoing of whatever karma
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.03,1:07:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,it may be undoing, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.42,1:07:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You try to have everything
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.92,1:07:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,subserve the good of all.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.67,1:08:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The next question is about meditation.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.34,1:08:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got them backwards.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.92,1:08:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,No wonder I can't read.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.18,1:08:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,As you see,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.43,1:08:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to hold your existence
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.89,1:08:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,in a certain,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.31,1:08:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,it's almost like a benediction.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.10,1:08:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's almost like
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.43,1:08:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,sanctifying one's own existence
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.35,1:08:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,by your posture vis-a-vis God.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.56,1:09:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,As far as sitting meditation,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.13,1:09:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,so this, in a way, is a meditation.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.84,1:09:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a way of being in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.81,1:09:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,in which one,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.85,1:09:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,as everything arises,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.47,1:09:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,one surrenders it to God
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.07,1:09:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,because to avoid
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.68,1:09:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,attractions and aversions,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.57,1:09:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,then one becomes detached
Dialogue: 0,1:09:17.85,1:09:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and one surrenders
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.36,1:09:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,all possibility to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.50,1:09:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,If this happens,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.65,1:09:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll go bankrupt.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.76,1:09:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if I go bankrupt,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.06,1:09:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I go bankrupt.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.00,1:09:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Lots of people survive bankruptcy.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.07,1:09:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,They still tend to be breathing and eating.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.81,1:09:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,If that's what it takes,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.13,1:09:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,if that's what it takes
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.18,1:09:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to get off materiality,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.55,1:09:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to get off pride of advantage,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.98,1:09:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,to get off the vanity of materialism,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:41.31,1:09:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,then I guess if it takes bankruptcy to do it,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.00,1:09:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,so let it be.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.94,1:09:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Bankruptcy is one of the ways to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.71,1:10:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,After you get rid of all the money
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.63,1:10:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and all the big cars
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.02,1:10:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and all the crap,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.93,1:10:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, you say,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.85,1:10:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm still me
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.40,1:10:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and I still enjoy fishing
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.71,1:10:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and life hasn't really changed at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.55,1:10:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.57,1:10:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Because love remains.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.34,1:10:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Love.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:18.50,1:10:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,There is formal meditation.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.28,1:10:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,There's meditation as a lifestyle.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.10,1:10:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So what I just described to you
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.40,1:10:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,was meditation as a mudra,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.32,1:10:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,as a lifestyle,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.05,1:10:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,which is itself a meditation.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:36.14,1:10:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Contemplation would be the next
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.17,1:10:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,more focused level
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.89,1:10:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,in which one is aware
Dialogue: 0,1:10:42.18,1:10:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,of the rising and the falling away
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.44,1:10:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,of the feelings, thoughts, and events
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.01,1:10:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,as they occur.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.42,1:10:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The focus is on that which is a priority.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.76,1:10:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is just before the arising,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.35,1:10:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,just before the arising of the thought and the feeling.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:59.02,1:11:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And then let go wanting to change it.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.56,1:11:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Let go resisting it.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.59,1:11:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And it rises, it crests,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:07.14,1:11:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and then it falls away
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.31,1:11:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,with no commentary.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.19,1:11:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a complete surrender to God
Dialogue: 0,1:11:21.61,1:11:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,in the everyday activities.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:25.51,1:11:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So you dedicate your life to God
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.21,1:11:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,by the way in which you are with the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:31.26,1:11:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,with the dedication,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:32.52,1:11:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,with the reverence
Dialogue: 0,1:11:33.26,1:11:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,with which you do everything
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.53,1:11:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,from digging a ditch
Dialogue: 0,1:11:35.80,1:11:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,to peeling a potato
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.72,1:11:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,to making dinner.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:37.73,1:11:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all the same.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:40.22,1:11:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all the same.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.42,1:11:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But it makes a difference.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:48.27,1:11:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The potato that's fueled by love
Dialogue: 0,1:11:50.05,1:11:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and cooked with love
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.09,1:11:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,is a different potato
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.77,1:11:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,than one that is chopped up by a machine.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.71,1:11:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:57.05,1:11:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody can check it out for themselves.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.07,1:12:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,More formal sitting meditation,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.34,1:12:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,a la Zen,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.82,1:12:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is a more disciplined,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.01,1:12:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,conscious, focused, concentrated,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.39,1:12:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,time-out from life
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.77,1:12:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,in which the focus can be
Dialogue: 0,1:12:20.15,1:12:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,a one-pointedness of mind
Dialogue: 0,1:12:22.47,1:12:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,on the thoughts as they arise.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.19,1:12:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And in this condition,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.98,1:12:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,one becomes,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:34.10,1:12:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,one transcends from the experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.81,1:12:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a chart that shows it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.68,1:12:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We showed it before.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:40.97,1:12:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You transcend identification
Dialogue: 0,1:12:42.63,1:12:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,with the thoughts
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.13,1:12:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and you become that which witnesses the thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:49.97,1:12:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:56.38,1:12:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, these are really,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:57.31,1:12:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,really the levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:12:58.42,1:13:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that strict meditation will take you through.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:02.10,1:13:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Strict meditation,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.26,1:13:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the mentation goes on and on.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.86,1:13:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way you can stop the mentation.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.06,1:13:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The mentation proliferates faster
Dialogue: 0,1:13:12.35,1:13:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,than you can counter it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:15.50,1:13:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So therefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:16.35,1:13:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,one has to transcend
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.56,1:13:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to become that which is
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.00,1:13:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,witnessing the mentation as it goes by.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:22.81,1:13:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The memories,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:23.39,1:13:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the fantasies,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:24.43,1:13:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the daydreams,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.89,1:13:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,little bits of music,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:28.64,1:13:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,ibbity-dibbity,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.39,1:13:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,boom,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.14,1:13:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,heady-fishies in an itty-bitty bowl,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:33.15,1:13:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,all this crap goes through your head.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:35.56,1:13:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't stop it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.38,1:13:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You know,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.88,1:13:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Hitler,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.27,1:13:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the third world war,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.15,1:13:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.52,1:13:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,all the wars,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.30,1:13:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,everything goes through your mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.60,1:13:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Little bits from childhood,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.32,1:13:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,little pieces of music,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:47.18,1:13:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,some vignette from a television commercial,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.68,1:13:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Bow Flux commercial.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.93,1:13:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I posed for that years ago
Dialogue: 0,1:13:58.97,1:13:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and they're still using it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:04.35,1:14:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,They asked me to do
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.35,1:14:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,a geriatric version of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:13.69,1:14:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,In which you only lose five pounds,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.60,1:14:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,not 400 pounds.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.84,1:14:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Five pounds will do.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.77,1:14:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So at first you're preoccupied with form
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.64,1:14:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and you begin to see that
Dialogue: 0,1:14:27.73,1:14:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,as we tried to stop your thoughts before,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.07,1:14:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,they won't stop.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:32.10,1:14:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They won't stop.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:33.93,1:14:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Something is registering those thoughts
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.06,1:14:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and recognizing them
Dialogue: 0,1:14:37.52,1:14:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and you realize,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.63,1:14:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that that within you is,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:41.06,1:14:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,while thoughts and all this is going on,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.63,1:14:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,something is witnessing them.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:46.36,1:14:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You say,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.17,1:14:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.60,1:14:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,George,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.90,1:14:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm thinking about so-and-so.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.51,1:14:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows or what is it
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.97,1:14:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that knows what you're thinking about?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.72,1:14:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's something beyond the thinkingness
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.14,1:14:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that is the witness of the thinkingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:00.02,1:15:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So you let go identifying with the thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:02.97,1:15:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.21,1:15:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't be the thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:04.28,1:15:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,If you were the thoughts,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:05.14,1:15:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,when you told them to stop,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:06.14,1:15:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,they'd stop.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:06.93,1:15:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.71,1:15:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,no,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.85,1:15:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you're the victim of the thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:10.55,1:15:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the victim of the thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:13.15,1:15:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it that's the victim of the thoughts?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.15,1:15:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The watcher,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.10,1:15:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the experiencer.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.22,1:15:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you know
Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.32,1:15:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that this watcher or experiencer
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.56,1:15:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,can report what it's reporting?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.28,1:15:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because there's a quality
Dialogue: 0,1:15:28.13,1:15:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and what we're looking for is a quality.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.71,1:15:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,A non-personal quality
Dialogue: 0,1:15:32.51,1:15:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,of awareness
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.98,1:15:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,behind the observer and the witness.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:37.85,1:15:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So in meditation,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:41.22,1:15:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,you're trying to sense.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:42.81,1:15:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it that exists
Dialogue: 0,1:15:44.50,1:15:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,prior to the thought?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.93,1:15:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it that the thoughts,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.85,1:15:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,how is it that they register?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:53.61,1:15:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,There is within, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.69,1:15:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,a quality to the consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:59.22,1:16:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The quality of consciousness itself,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.42,1:16:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,which itself is silent.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:05.88,1:16:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because of the silence,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:07.92,1:16:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the background silence,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:09.14,1:16:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that you can hear sound.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:11.27,1:16:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,All right,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:11.60,1:16:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you can focus either on the sound
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.52,1:16:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,or the silence that makes detecting
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.34,1:16:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the sound possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:19.81,1:16:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Similarly,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.84,1:16:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,you can focus on consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.84,1:16:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,which itself is without form,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:27.14,1:16:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,but which illuminates all form.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.02,1:16:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And you begin to withdraw from the thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:32.27,1:16:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The thoughts are changing all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:33.81,1:16:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That can't be who you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:34.94,1:16:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You would have been dead a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:38.39,1:16:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So one withdraws one's identification
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.61,1:16:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,to the more detached.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.93,1:16:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We use the analogy also
Dialogue: 0,1:16:47.02,1:16:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,of content versus context.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:49.51,1:16:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The thoughts themselves
Dialogue: 0,1:16:52.38,1:16:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,are the content.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:54.26,1:16:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But what is the overall context
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.31,1:16:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,which is holding this capacity
Dialogue: 0,1:16:58.92,1:17:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,for thought and feeling and all
Dialogue: 0,1:17:01.14,1:17:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,in the first place?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.68,1:17:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What is a priority?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.27,1:17:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What is more prior?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.18,1:17:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You go through the whole story
Dialogue: 0,1:17:08.34,1:17:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,of your job with so-and-so
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.81,1:17:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and how they screwed you
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.02,1:17:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and didn't give you the raise you would do.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.68,1:17:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So you go through these stories,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:18.93,1:17:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,laments from the past,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:20.97,1:17:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,or daydreams of the future,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:22.17,1:17:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,but they're all stories.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.14,1:17:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the willingness to surrender
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.51,1:17:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the storiness of this recollection to God
Dialogue: 0,1:17:28.56,1:17:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,begins to shorten it.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.64,1:17:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Letting go of the wanting to think.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:34.36,1:17:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So you'll find that thinking
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.89,1:17:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,is coming out of a wanting to think.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.27,1:17:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a desire to think.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:40.75,1:17:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:41.31,1:17:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,we think thoughts are wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.47,1:17:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason we think they're wonderful
Dialogue: 0,1:17:44.68,1:17:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,is because they're our thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:47.67,1:17:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody else's thoughts
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.82,1:17:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,are not really all that charming
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.22,1:17:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,when you think of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:52.22,1:17:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Honey, would you like to hear
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.11,1:17:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,what I think?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.53,1:17:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think about now?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:58.81,1:18:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so we're enamored of thoughts
Dialogue: 0,1:18:01.56,1:18:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,because they're our thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.32,1:18:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,If they're our thoughts,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.27,1:18:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,they're wonderful, precious, and valuable.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:06.51,1:18:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,If they're somebody else's thoughts,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:08.44,1:18:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,they're stupid.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.82,1:18:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So we get to the core of thinking this,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.40,1:18:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the narcissistic,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:15.98,1:18:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,egocentric investment in them.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:21.17,1:18:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Thoughts are wonderful, valuable,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.56,1:18:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and valid
Dialogue: 0,1:18:24.32,1:18:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,because they're ours.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.86,1:18:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,My thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:30.15,1:18:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The way you get off that,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.42,1:18:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,is you realize that thinkingness
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.02,1:18:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,is happening of itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.00,1:18:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,They aren't your thoughts at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.53,1:18:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,As you look at the energy fields of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.84,1:18:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,there are huge thought fields
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.76,1:18:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,in which your consciousness is immersed.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:46.47,1:18:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And the thinkingness of all of mankind
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.30,1:18:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is what's programming your head,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.85,1:18:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,together with last night's TV news, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.61,1:18:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We get off the vanity.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.06,1:18:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's a secret vanity
Dialogue: 0,1:18:59.73,1:19:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to the thinkingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.27,1:19:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The thinkingness also brings us back to the thought.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:03.88,1:19:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It brings up a feelingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:05.00,1:19:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And you'll notice that all thinkingness has a payoff.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.35,1:19:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You're getting one up on something.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:13.06,1:19:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You're getting even with something.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.97,1:19:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,When you think negative thoughts about people,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:18.98,1:19:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,secretly you're punishing them.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.14,1:19:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That crazy old bitch.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.52,1:19:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That nutty old man.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:28.11,1:19:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He deserves arthritis.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:31.52,1:19:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We get a secret getting even kind of feeling.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:34.56,1:19:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We write wrongs.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.72,1:19:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We write these wonderful stories in our head.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.50,1:19:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,How we write these wrongs.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.27,1:19:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,How the guilty are made to pay.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.80,1:19:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So, all right.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:53.81,1:19:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, this thinkingness happens
Dialogue: 0,1:19:56.07,1:19:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,because there's a desire to think.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.06,1:20:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Because there's a secret payoff to thinkingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:02.48,1:20:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we think that thinkingness is valuable.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.67,1:20:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's coming from an energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.71,1:20:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a root to thinkingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:12.65,1:20:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,As you let go,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.93,1:20:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,wanting to dramatize
Dialogue: 0,1:20:16.84,1:20:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,everything into the form of thinkingness,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:18.69,1:20:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,into the form of a story,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:21.15,1:20:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll see the self-indulgence of that
Dialogue: 0,1:20:23.31,1:20:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and the egocentricity if you look at it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:26.10,1:20:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,As your head manufactures these stories,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:28.56,1:20:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,it's strictly egocentric.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:30.72,1:20:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's strictly narcissistic.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:33.06,1:20:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very self-indulgent.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:36.47,1:20:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You see that the ego is in love with itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.39,1:20:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's getting an enormous payoff
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.01,1:20:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,from all this thinkingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.52,1:20:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You decide to turn the pleasure,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:48.64,1:20:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the secret pleasure of thinkingness
Dialogue: 0,1:20:50.35,1:20:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,over and surrender it to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:51.84,1:20:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,As you let go,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:57.97,1:20:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,wanting to make stories,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:59.78,1:21:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,they become paragraphs.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.14,1:21:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,As you let go,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.78,1:21:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,wanting to write paragraphs,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.17,1:21:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,they become short sentences.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.94,1:21:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you begin to see
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.06,1:21:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the unloggy of thoughts as they arise.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:11.27,1:21:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like there's a primordial energy bed
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.72,1:21:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,which is not yet into form.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.32,1:21:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It wants to come into form.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:22.53,1:21:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It starts to think dog.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:25.42,1:21:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it thinks about old Bawa,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.47,1:21:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and you remember how old Bawa was sick.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:29.38,1:21:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You remember how Bawa used to bring the paper in.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:31.38,1:21:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You remember how the kids used to play with Bawa.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:33.96,1:21:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's a whole story about Bawa.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:35.97,1:21:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Pretty soon you're weeping
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.85,1:21:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,thinking about when Bawa died.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:39.46,1:21:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa, I mean, it just grows, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:43.21,1:21:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so there has to be a willingness
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.77,1:21:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to surrender all that.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:47.01,1:21:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The sentimentality,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:49.38,1:21:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the validation of yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:21:50.93,1:21:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,as the good pet owner or whatever.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.68,1:21:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The letting go of the sadness
Dialogue: 0,1:21:55.90,1:21:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,of the thinking of the good old days, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.39,1:22:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, the long story about Bawa
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.26,1:22:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,borrows down to a paragraph,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:04.89,1:22:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,then it comes down to a sentence.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.26,1:22:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you catch the mind
Dialogue: 0,1:22:08.38,1:22:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,starting to think about Bawa,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.56,1:22:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and you surrender it at that point.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:12.57,1:22:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's a constant surrenderingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.51,1:22:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,As you do this,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:16.67,1:22:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,what happens is you nip thoughts in the bud.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.85,1:22:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll see they're coming out
Dialogue: 0,1:22:20.82,1:22:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,of a formless unloggy,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:23.68,1:22:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,free form, you might say.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:26.06,1:22:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't quite dogginess yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:27.96,1:22:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And the word dog doesn't exist yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.30,1:22:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But image of dogginess,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:31.43,1:22:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,all this happens very rapidly,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:34.11,1:22:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's continuous.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.69,1:22:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's like a continuous fount
Dialogue: 0,1:22:37.46,1:22:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,of thinkingness coming out of a
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.19,1:22:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,energy field that we could just call
Dialogue: 0,1:22:42.52,1:22:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,thinkingness,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:44.43,1:22:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy like a fountain
Dialogue: 0,1:22:47.14,1:22:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,out of which proliferates
Dialogue: 0,1:22:49.06,1:22:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,thinkingness endlessly.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:52.02,1:22:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,One surrenders this to God
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.53,1:22:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,at greater and greater depth
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.14,1:22:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,until finally one gets to the very core
Dialogue: 0,1:22:57.30,1:22:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,of thinkingness itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.64,1:23:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And one surrenders
Dialogue: 0,1:23:01.14,1:23:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the identification of self
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.88,1:23:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,as thinkingness
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.00,1:23:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and surrenders thinkingness to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.10,1:23:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That is quite a sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:17.64,1:23:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you be willing to become
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.72,1:23:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,a dumb animal who doesn't think?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:22.86,1:23:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You can become a happy dog,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.52,1:23:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,but you're not going to be able
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.44,1:23:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,to think again.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.00,1:23:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be a happy purring kitty,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:32.84,1:23:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,but you won't be allowed
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.65,1:23:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to think anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:38.96,1:23:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:41.36,1:23:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't think if I'm a kitty?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:45.19,1:23:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You can purr.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.40,1:23:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.68,1:23:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't think anymore, God?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:53.35,1:23:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to be a kitty.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:58.69,1:24:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the identification of self
Dialogue: 0,1:24:00.76,1:24:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,is thinkingness is part and parcel
Dialogue: 0,1:24:03.97,1:24:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,of identifying yourself as ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:06.72,1:24:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,as human ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:09.46,1:24:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And you'll see the great reluctance
Dialogue: 0,1:24:11.15,1:24:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,with which you let go
Dialogue: 0,1:24:12.39,1:24:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and the tenacity with which you let
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.26,1:24:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,hang on to thinkingness
Dialogue: 0,1:24:15.73,1:24:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,despite your lamenting it.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:18.30,1:24:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody laments their thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:20.00,1:24:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I was laying in bed
Dialogue: 0,1:24:20.68,1:24:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and I couldn't go to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.61,1:24:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I kept coming back and back.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.11,1:24:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody laments their thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:24.85,1:24:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,If you really lamented your thoughts,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:26.96,1:24:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,they would stop.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:30.38,1:24:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So you think you're lamenting your thoughts,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:32.88,1:24:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,but you're secretly delighting
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.77,1:24:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,in their torment.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:36.35,1:24:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And you have to give up
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.32,1:24:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the secret delight in the torment.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:42.19,1:24:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So in really intense meditation then,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:45.60,1:24:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,there is a willingness
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.65,1:24:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,to surrender everything to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:50.82,1:24:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Thinkingness itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:52.40,1:24:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you end up surrendering
Dialogue: 0,1:24:54.01,1:24:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,is mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.94,1:24:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The willingness to surrender mind,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:57.93,1:24:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:58.27,1:24:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Itself to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.36,1:25:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you discover
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.36,1:25:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,there isn't such a thing as mind anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:05.21,1:25:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.02,1:25:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.67,1:25:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And as thoughts disappear,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:10.10,1:25:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,so does mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:12.60,1:25:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no such thing as mind
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.56,1:25:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,any more than there is such a thing as ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.05,1:25:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But for spiritual work,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.14,1:25:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,we call the ego the ego
Dialogue: 0,1:25:23.67,1:25:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,at least for a period of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.02,1:25:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we reach a certain level
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.52,1:25:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,where we realize there is no such structure
Dialogue: 0,1:25:29.64,1:25:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and only our belief systems
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.10,1:25:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,work.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.52,1:25:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we start holding it in place
Dialogue: 0,1:25:34.52,1:25:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and that it is not really an it at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:36.52,1:25:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't have any independent existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.52,1:25:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Formal sitting meditation
Dialogue: 0,1:25:43.65,1:25:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is in itself an end.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.65,1:25:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And many people have spent
Dialogue: 0,1:25:47.65,1:25:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,many a lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:49.65,1:25:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,many years in a strict meditation.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:51.89,1:25:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I myself spent
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.89,1:25:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how many lifetimes
Dialogue: 0,1:25:55.89,1:25:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,in meditation.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:58.52,1:26:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It is, of course, classically
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.52,1:26:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the way of non-duality,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.52,1:26:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the royal road to God through non-duality.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:04.52,1:26:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The quote is,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.93,1:26:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the core is Zen practice,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:07.93,1:26:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and many other practices,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:11.30,1:26:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,not just Zen.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:13.56,1:26:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Any one of the meditative practices
Dialogue: 0,1:26:18.42,1:26:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,can bring you into various levels of satori.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.42,1:26:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,These levels of satori
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.53,1:26:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,are sudden flashes where you transcend mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.82,1:26:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Ambiguities are resolved
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.82,1:26:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,because you see the positionality
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.82,1:26:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that was creating the apparent opposites
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.82,1:26:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and they suddenly collapse.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:37.82,1:26:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And
Dialogue: 0,1:26:38.82,1:26:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,so meditation itself
Dialogue: 0,1:26:41.78,1:26:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is certainly a worthy endeavor.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.14,1:26:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,One's dedication of meditation to God
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.27,1:26:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of looking for a benefit.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.30,1:26:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So the other block to get out of the way
Dialogue: 0,1:26:56.61,1:27:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,is to stop meditating for something.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:00.93,1:27:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,One cannot meditate in order to reach satori,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.93,1:27:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to reach enlightenment,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:05.93,1:27:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to realize one's Buddha nature.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.93,1:27:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,One meditates for the sake of meditation
Dialogue: 0,1:27:10.93,1:27:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,period.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.93,1:27:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Not because it will get you anything,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:14.93,1:27:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,get you anywhere,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.93,1:27:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,not for any alleged or imagined gain.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.02,1:27:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:24.02,1:27:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,To sacrifice all goal.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:26.97,1:27:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I meditate
Dialogue: 0,1:27:31.18,1:27:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,out of devotion to Thee, O Lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:34.18,1:27:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Period.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:41.07,1:27:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Formal sitting meditation can last.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.07,1:27:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I did it for 20 years,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:44.07,1:27:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,an hour in the morning,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:45.07,1:27:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,an hour at night.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.07,1:27:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,When you had more time,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:47.10,1:27:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to meditate six hours a day
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.10,1:27:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,or eight hours a day
Dialogue: 0,1:27:50.10,1:27:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and then I went into
Dialogue: 0,1:27:51.10,1:27:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,24 hour day meditation.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.10,1:27:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Since then I haven't meditated at all.
